🚀 DEPLOYMENT ARCHITECTURE & SETUP
📌 1. Deployment Overview

The Smart Student Connect system is deployed as a full-stack web application integrated with ServiceNow backend APIs and React frontend, ensuring scalability, accessibility, and real-time data synchronization.

The deployment follows a cloud-based client-server architecture.

🧱 2. Deployment Architecture
        ┌──────────────────────────────┐
        │        USER BROWSER          │
        │  (Student / Faculty / Admin)│
        └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                       │ HTTPS Request
                       ▼
        ┌──────────────────────────────┐
        │     FRONTEND (React/Web)     │
        │  - UI Components             │
        │  - AppContext API Layer      │
        │  - Service Layer             │
        └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                       │ REST API Calls
                       ▼
        ┌──────────────────────────────┐
        │   SERVICE LAYER (API BRIDGE) │
        │  - ServiceNow API Calls      │
        │  - Authentication Handling   │
        │  - Data Processing           │
        └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
        ┌──────────────────────────────┐
        │    SERVICE NOW PLATFORM      │
        │  - Tables                   │
        │  - Flow Designer            │
        │  - Business Rules           │
        │  - ACL Security             │
        └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
        ┌──────────────────────────────┐
        │        DATABASE LAYER        │
        │ student / task / request DB  │
        └──────────────────────────────┘
⚙️ 3. Deployment Steps
🟢 STEP 1: Frontend Deployment
Build React application:
npm run build
Host using:
Netlify / Vercel / AWS S3
🟢 STEP 2: ServiceNow Backend Setup
Configure ServiceNow instance
Create tables:
student_table
task_table
request_table
Enable:
Business Rules
Flow Designer
ACL security rules
🟢 STEP 3: API Integration
Connect frontend with ServiceNow using REST API:
fetch("https://instance.service-now.com/api/now/table/student_table", {
  method: "GET",
  headers: {
    "Authorization": "Bearer <token>",
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
  }
});
🟢 STEP 4: Authentication Deployment
Unified authentication using AppContext.tsx
Token-based session handling
Secure login for all roles
🟢 STEP 5: AI Module Deployment
AI services integrated into backend layer:
Performance prediction engine
Smart scoring logic
Chatbot (Virtual Agent integration)
🔐 4. Security in Deployment
HTTPS secured communication
Role-Based Access Control (ACL)
API authentication via tokens
Data encryption at rest and in transit
📊 5. CI/CD (Optional but HIGH SCORE BOOST)
GitHub integration for version control
Auto deployment using:
GitHub Actions / Vercel pipeline
Continuous updates for frontend + backend
🏆 6. FINAL DEPLOYMENT SUMMARY (ADD IN REPORT)

The system is deployed using a cloud-based architecture integrating a React frontend, ServiceNow backend platform, and API-driven service layer. It ensures secure, scalable, and real-time data communication between users and system modules. AI-based components are deployed within the ServiceNow ecosystem to enhance predictive analytics and decision-making.
